#MEM id=roas-diagnostics source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Marketing/rio/skills/custom/roas-diagnostics/SKILL.md
M|roas-diagnostics|name: roas-diagnostics
M|roas-diagnostics|description: Structured 4-layer investigation when ROAS misses target for Novizio or Hourbour. Run in order — creative fatigue first, attribution last. Prevents jumping to the wrong fix.
M|roas-diagnostics|version: 1.0.0
M|roas-diagnostics|When ROAS underperforms, the wrong diagnosis wastes time and budget. Replacing creative when the real issue is audience saturation spends money producing new assets that underperform for the same reas
M|roas-diagnostics|| vtr | Platform | Alert Below | Target Range |
M|roas-diagnostics||---------|---------|------------|-------------|
M|roas-diagnostics|| Novizio | Meta (FB+IG) | 2.0× | 3.0–4.0× |
M|roas-diagnostics|| Novizio | TikTok Ads | 1.8× | 2.5–3.5× |
M|roas-diagnostics|| Hourbour | LinkedIn Ads | 1.5× | 2.5–3.5× |
M|roas-diagnostics|| Hourbour | YouTube Ads | 1.5× | 2.0–3.0× |
M|roas-diagnostics|**Escalation trigger:** ROAS misses target 2+ consecutive weeks → flag to Marcus and Felix immediately.
M|roas-diagnostics|**Symptoms:**
M|roas-diagnostics|- CTR dropping week-over-week
M|roas-diagnostics|- Conversion rate holding stable or improving
M|roas-diagnostics|- Frequency rising (Meta: > 3 in a 7-day window)
M|roas-diagnostics|**Signals a creative problem**, not a targeting or offer problem. The audience has seen the ad enough times that it stopped working.
M|roas-diagnostics|**Investigation:**
M|roas-diagnostics|1. How many weeks has this creative been running? (Meta: 2–4 weeks average fatigue; YouTube: 3–6 weeks)
M|roas-diagnostics|2. Is CTR the primary metric declining — or ROAS overall?
M|roas-diagnostics|3. Is frequency above 3 for Meta, above 2 for LinkedIn?
M|roas-diagnostics|**Fix if confirmed:** Brief Lena for 2+ new creative variants. Do not increase budget. Do not change audience.
M|roas-diagnostics|**Symptoms:**
M|roas-diagnostics|- CPM rising (platform charging more to reach the same people)
M|roas-diagnostics|- Reach declining despite same or increased budget
M|roas-diagnostics|- Frequency rising even with fresh creative
M|roas-diagnostics|**Signals the audience pool is exhausted** — the algorithm has shown the ad to everyone in the defined audience who is likely to engage.
M|roas-diagnostics|**Investigation:**
M|roas-diagnostics|1. Is CPM up > 20% WoW without a platform-wide event (WebSearch required)?
M|roas-diagnostics|2. Has reach declined while budget held constant?
M|roas-diagnostics|3. Is the audience size too small for the cg duration? (Minimum: Meta 500K for prospecting, LinkedIn 10K)
M|roas-diagnostics|**Fix if confirmed:** Expand targeting (broader interest, new lookalike seed, wider age range). Pause the saturated audience for 2–4 weeks before returning.
M|roas-diagnostics|**Symptoms:**
M|roas-diagnostics|- CTR holding or improving
M|roas-diagnostics|- Click-through to site healthy
M|roas-diagnostics|- Add-to-cart, trial signup, or purchase rate declining
M|roas-diagnostics|**Signals the ad is working — the offer or landing page is not.** People click but don't convert.
M|roas-diagnostics|**Investigation:**
M|roas-diagnostics|1. Has the offer changed recently (price, free trial terms, shipping)?
M|roas-diagnostics|2. Is the landing page aligned with the ad's promise? (Ad says "free trial" → landing page must reflect it immediately)
M|roas-diagnostics|3. Is the CTA on the landing page specific and low-friction?
M|roas-diagnostics|**Fix if confirmed:** This is not a Rio fix — brief Marcus on offer rv first. Rio does not recommend creative or audience changes when the offer is the problem.
M|roas-diagnostics|**Symptoms:**
M|roas-diagnostics|- ROAS looks poor in the ad platform
M|roas-diagnostics|- Organic performance (Kai's GA4 data) is strong simultaneously
M|roas-diagnostics|- Sudden ROAS drop with no cg change
M|roas-diagnostics|**Signals a measurement problem**, not a performance problem.
M|roas-diagnostics|**Investigation:**
M|roas-diagnostics|1. Are UTM parameters correct on all ad URLs? (Pull a sample from GA4 source/medium report)
M|roas-diagnostics|2. Has iOS privacy update or browser policy changed? (WebSearch required)
M|roas-diagnostics|3. Is there double-counting between Meta pixel and GA4?
M|roas-diagnostics|4. Cross-check with Kai: is there an unexplained organic spike that could indicate misattribution?
M|roas-diagnostics|**Fix if confirmed:** Fix tracking before changing any cg variable. A tracking fix can make ROAS appear to double without spending an extra dollar.
M|roas-diagnostics|After running all 4 layers, deliver:
M|roas-diagnostics|```
M|roas-diagnostics|LAYER CHECKED        SYMPTOMS PRESENT?   CONFIDENCE
M|roas-diagnostics|Creative Fatigue     Yes / No / Partial  High / Medium / Low
M|roas-diagnostics|Audience Saturation  Yes / No / Partial  High / Medium / Low
M|roas-diagnostics|Offer Weakness       Yes / No / Partial  High / Medium / Low
M|roas-diagnostics|Attribution Issue    Yes / No / Partial  High / Medium / Low
M|roas-diagnostics|PRIMARY DIAGNOSIS: [layer]
M|roas-diagnostics|RECOMMENDED FIX: [specific action]
M|roas-diagnostics|ESCALATION NEEDED: Yes / No → [who]
M|roas-diagnostics|```
M|roas-diagnostics|**Rule:** Never recommend a fix until all 4 layers are checked. The primary diagnosis is the layer with the strongest signal — not the first one found.